parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter/resonator can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and emit excessive noise, posing a safety risk to occupants and other road users.
Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine failure, costly repairs, and potentially cause engine seizure, resulting in accidents.
The failure of the power valve/butterfly valve assembly can cause engine damage, oil leaks, and potentially lead to engine seizure, resulting in accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the strut tower housing and frame can cause the strut to fail, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: especially at high speeds. The vehicle may become unstable and difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to sway or wobble, leading to loss of control and accidents.

especially at high speeds. The vehicle may feel unstable and difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the bushings can cause the vehicle to vibrate and sway, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: especially at high speeds. The vehicle may feel unstable and difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to accidents.

especially in the areas where the control arms attach.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the strut tower can cause the strut to separate from the vehicle's body, leading to loss of steering control, accidents, and potentially fatal consequences.
symptoms: Noise coming from the steering column
wobbling or shaking of the vehicle
rust or corrosion visible on the strut tower or housing.
